To multiply and simplify:

\[
\frac{5}{12}\times\frac{8}{9}
\]

1. Factor and cancel common factors between numerators and denominators. Notice \(8\) and \(12\) share a factor of 4:
\[
\frac{5}{\cancel{12}}\times\frac{\cancel{8}}{9}
\;\longrightarrow\;
\frac{5}{3}\times\frac{2}{9}
\]
2. Multiply across:
\[
\frac{5\cdot2}{3\cdot9}
=
\frac{10}{27}
\]
Since \(10/27<1\), as a mixed number it remains \(10/27\).
